terms of how you feel motion

00:11:44.310 --> 00:11:49.530
is that you have fluid
moving in your ear canal.

00:11:49.530 --> 00:11:51.760
You can't actually
really detect the fluid.

00:11:51.760 --> 00:11:56.890
What happens is you have these
little hairs that come up.

00:11:56.890 --> 00:12:01.320
And so when the fluid
changes direction--

00:12:01.320 --> 00:12:03.690
so let's say that the
fluid starts moving

00:12:03.690 --> 00:12:05.640
in a particular direction.

00:12:05.640 --> 00:12:11.530
Then all these hair
pieces start moving,

00:12:11.530 --> 00:12:14.510
and so you feel that motion.

00:12:14.510 --> 00:12:19.150
Now, the fluid can continue
to move in that direction.

00:12:19.150 --> 00:12:25.540
But over time,
the hair follicles

00:12:25.540 --> 00:12:28.630
will basically resume
where they are.

00:12:28.630 --> 00:12:31.690
They won't feel
motion occurring.

00:12:31.690 --> 00:12:34.520
Or they'll basically
be stagnant.

00:12:34.520 --> 00:12:36.710
So it could be the case
that the fluid is moving,

00:12:36.710 --> 00:12:40.390
and the hair is
sitting like this.

00:12:40.390 --> 00:12:49.060
Now, all of a sudden, when
the fluid stops moving,

00:12:49.060 --> 00:12:54.430
the hair tries to just
return to its previous state.

00:12:54.430 --> 00:12:56.680
And when that happens,
you might actually

00:12:56.680 --> 00:13:01.190
think that you've started
moving in the other direction.

00:13:01.190 --> 00:13:04.090
So this is an issue
where, basically,

00:13:04.090 --> 00:13:07.780
if you are flying along
and you start turning

00:13:07.780 --> 00:13:11.200
and you're in a
constant rate turn,

00:13:11.200 --> 00:13:15.340
you might start feeling
like you're not turning.

00:13:15.340 --> 00:13:18.580
And then, when you come out
of that turn-- so you roll out

00:13:18.580 --> 00:13:20.590
and now you're straight
and level again,

00:13:20.590 --> 00:13:24.940
you feel like you have just
started turning to the right.

00:13:24.940 --> 00:13:27.220
So even though now you're
flying straight and level,

00:13:27.220 --> 00:13:30.820
your ear is telling you that
you've turned to the right.

00:13:30.820 --> 00:13:34.180
And so you tried to correct that
by turning back to the left.

00:13:34.180 --> 00:13:37.480
So it might be the case that
your airplane's actual motion

00:13:37.480 --> 00:13:40.623
was constant rate turned to the
left and then it flattened out,

00:13:40.623 --> 00:13:42.040
but you don't
realize you're flat.

00:13:42.040 --> 00:13:44.330
So you start turning again.

00:13:44.330 --> 00:13:46.510
So these are reasons
why you don't

00:13:46.510 --> 00:13:48.640
want to rely on your inner ear.

